# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.DS_Store

# Large generated catalog (~72 MB). Regenerate with src/darkproteome/ingest_atlases.py
# from the atlas sources documented in data/SOURCES.md. Smaller derived tables ARE tracked
# (claim_catalog_real.csv, claim_catalog_scored.csv).
data/claim_catalog_scaled.csv

# Large public external inputs (~168 MB: SwissProt, IEAtlas, CrypticProteinDB, HLA Ligand
# Atlas, the 2 cohort supplements). Not committed (size + redistribution terms).
# src/darkproteome/paths.py resolves them; re-download via data/external/README.md +
# data/SOURCES.md. The recovery README itself stays tracked.
data/external/*
!data/external/README.md

# manuscript/manuscript.pdf is the canonical, tracked PDF (GitHub renders it inline for
# readers; rebuild via tectonic then `cp manuscript/tex/manuscript.pdf manuscript/manuscript.pdf`
# after editing manuscript.md). The raw tex/ build output itself stays gitignored -- it's an
# intermediate, not the copy readers see.
manuscript/tex/manuscript.pdf
